ARTICLE 3  -  GPT3 
== SOURCE
https://www.forbes.com/sites/bernardmarr/2020/10/05/what-is-gpt-3-and-why-is-it-revolutionizing-artificial-intelligence/?sh=5bf9482e481a
https://lambdalabs.com/blog/demystifying-gpt-3/

== AGENT
OpenAI

== GOAL
It aims simply to be able to perform text generation

== DATA
It was trained with text from Books, Wikipedia, Common Crawl and Text from the internet.

== METHODS
Deep learning 

== RESULTS
GPT-3 can create anything that has a language structure  -  which means it can answer questions, write essays, summarize long texts, translate languages, take memos, and even create computer code

== ISSUES
The amount of computing power required to run GPT3 are hugely expensive and makes it not able to work for most people

== SCORE
8

== COMMENTS
It is interesting a program that can write articles just like this https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2020/sep/08/robot-wrote-this-article-gpt-3 so it is nice to see 
